@startuml Component Diagram - Layer 2: State Management (Simplified)
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml
title Layer 2: State Management (RxJS BehaviorSubject - Single Source of Truth)

Container_Boundary(renderer, "Renderer Process (Angular)") {

    Component(nav_state, "Navigation State", "BehaviorSubject<T>", "route$: Current route\nactiveTab$: Active tab")
    
    Component(import_state, "Import State", "BehaviorSubject<T>", "dipTree$: Document tree\nselectedDocument$: Current selection\nimportStatus$: Load state")
    
    Component(search_state, "Search State", "BehaviorSubject<T>", "searchResults$: Text results\nsemanticResults$: Semantic results")
}

note as state_management
  **Layer 2: State Management**
  
  Pattern: RxJS Observer (no NgRx/Redux)
  
  Each BehaviorSubject:
  ✓ Holds current state
  ✓ Emits changes to subscribers
  ✓ Replays last value for new subscribers
  ✓ Type-safe with TypeScript generics
  
  Components subscribe with async pipe:
  {{ element | async }}
  
  Services update observables:
  this.state.next(newValue)
  
  Benefits:
  • No Redux boilerplate
  • Smaller bundle size
  • Simpler debugging
  • Reactive by default
end note

@enduml
